subject: Change message_registries namespace to registries
commitMessage:
Change message_registries namespace to registries

The message_registries namespace is overly wordy, and results in very
long defines.  Doing this one minor change reduces the code by 50 lines.
This seems worthwhile.

Tested: Unit tests pass.  Namespace change only.

Signed-off-by: Ed Tanous <edtanous@google.com>
Change-Id: Ib1401580b3fa47596eb56cdc86e60eeeb1c2f952

Seems reasonable
So these 3 message_registries change and clang-format reformats the entire function? Anything else non-white space change?

Yep.  This patchset is literally a find and replace of message_registry with registry, then a re-clang-format , and it does crazy things like this.

Admittedly, this code would ideally be broken down into some smaller functions before merge, but that's spilled milk under the bridge.

clang-formats tabbing of lambdas seems to have some basis on how long the longest line is within the method, and is kind of subjective.  That's largely why I really want to move away from direct lambda callbacks, as it leads to crazy diffs like this on seemingly minor changes.
